ITMgGQJoiJEMGjIDkiGAhhjJoCEzIBkCaIiRDBoyA5IhgIYYyaAhMw0hGQB4
teFXMgAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA
AAAAAAAANBD/AS7QH7U=
     "], {{0, 155.}, {273., 0}}, {0, 255},
     ColorFunction->RGBColor,
     ImageResolution->{72., 72.},
     RasterInterpolation->"High"],
    BoxForm`ImageTag["Byte", ColorSpace -> "RGB", Interleaving -> True],
    Selectable->False],
   DefaultBaseStyle->"ImageGraphics",
   ImageSize->Automatic,
   ImageSizeRaw->{273., 155.},
   PlotRange->{{0, 273.}, {0, 155.}}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->
  "415357b1-2148-4528-9da4-b60bbfa6c911"],
 "\n",
 "(a) What is the probability that a cow is infected and has been transported \
by a truck\nrecently?\n(b) What is the probability of having an infected cow \
given that it has been transported\nby the truck?\n(c) Determine and \
interpret P (B) ."
}], "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947898734573824*^9, 3.9478987782361593`*^9}, 
   3.947898850129445*^9},ExpressionUUID->"c833d8aa-1077-40bf-b106-\
97fe840a3855"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "(a) The \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]and\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] operator refers \
to the joint distribution of two variables. In our example, we want to know \
the probability of being infected and having been transported by the truck. \
This probability can be directly obtained from the respective entry in the \
contingency table: 40 out of 200 cows fulfil both criteria and thus\nP(B \
\:2229 A) = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["40", "200"], "=", "0.2"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6e7520ce-5382-4e97-bdd7-4cb09b01135f"],
 ".\n\n(b) We can use P(A) = 100/200= P(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4624cce4-d3b3-42e1-941e-56657f40d47f"],
 ") to obtain:\nP(B|A) = P(B \:2229 A)/P(A)= (40/200)/(100/200)=40/100=0.4.\n\
\n(c) Using these results and P(B) = 60/200 , and P(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["B", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{B}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dbf9b325-7c00-451e-b39c-322ba56251b2"],
 ") = 140/200= 1 \[Minus] P(B), we obtain\nP(B|",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e6ded414-d2f5-4315-a222-3eed72b37810"],
 ") = P(B \:2229",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1cab255e-199b-435d-b4fd-693fdeb88d42"],
 " )/P(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bd762bee-901f-46bf-99c3-19614a5e2f45"],
 ")= (20/200)/(100/200)= 20/100=0.2\nby using the Law of Total Probability. \
We can thus calculate\nP(B) = P(B|A)P(A) + P(B|",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1c47b39f-fd1e-49eb-b006-a5030ae3e988"],
 ")P(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], "_"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\overline{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f740fb3-deff-4370-89fb-e915bb163754"],
 ")= 0.40 \[CenterDot] 0.50 + 0.20 \[CenterDot] 0.50 = 0.30.\nThis means that \
the probability of a cow being infected is 30 %. Alternatively, we could have \
simply looked at the marginal distribution of the contingency table to get \
P(B) = 60/200 = 0.3."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947900641222848*^9, 3.947900698747813*^9}, {
  3.947900831628601*^9, 3.947901032044681*^9}, {3.947901066265298*^9, 
  3.947901101269786*^9}, {3.947901195232675*^9, 3.947901283522821*^9}, {
  3.947901333298438*^9, 3.9479013399706383`*^9}, {3.951014780069254*^9, 
  3.951014780685348*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5bc9fc91-dae1-4576-82bb-\
ffed074c0c98"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
